issue.title: The files of the icons info.exult.exult(.studio).svg are big
issue.body:
- `info.exult.exult.svg` is 270 K, `info.exult.exult.studio.svg` is 210 K, mostly because they contain a 16 K javascipt script, replicated 8 times in `info.exult.exult.studio.svg`, replicated 15 times in `info.exult.exult.svg`.

If I remove the scripts, I get a seemingly identical image, but 14 K for `info.exult.exult.svg` :

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eb365faf-fd79-47d6-ad42-095c31e7a08e)

and 92K for `info.exult.exult.studio.svg` :

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/24339636-8658-490f-ba75-2ac50f9d1077)

@fpiesche, would you like to validate the reduced size icons above ? 
Just right click on them and Save as, as they are the SVG I obtained after slicing off the scripts, just renamed.

comment.body:
On macOS the SVGs are not installed. Application bundles use ICNS files for their application icon.
If you have a GTK based app you need to bundle the icon schemes in your app bundle to use it.
Not too long ago, I tested this with a previous patch of yours and the icon showed when bundled, I will try tomorrow again but it works in some way for sure.

An app bundle is laid out like this (a folder called Exult_Studio.app and this content):

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/191370b2-ea6e-4b6d-89cd-31b7d369a554)
